{"title":"Shadows","url":"http://crawl.chaosforge.org/Shadows","type":"markdown","data":"***Version [0.28](/0.28 \"0.28\")**: This article **may not be** up to date for the [latest stable release](/0.32 \"0.32\") of Crawl.*\n\n|   |                                                                |\n| - | -------------------------------------------------------------- |\n|   | It reduces the distance the wearer can be seen at and can see. |\n\n**Shadows** is an [ego](/Ego \"Ego\") found on [scarves](/Scarves \"Scarves\"). A scarf of shadows reduces your [LOS](/LOS \"LOS\") by 1, in turn reducing the distance you can attack or be attacked at.\n\n## Strategy\n\n- Useful when trying to sneakily steal a [rune of Zot](/Rune_of_Zot \"Rune of Zot\"). Or to be sneaky in general; less sight means less chances for a monster to wake before you [stab](/Stab \"Stab\") them.\n  - [Kobolds](/Kobold \"Kobold\") have their LOS reduced to 3, which is even tinier.\n- Scarves of shadow are also useful if you struggle with ranged enemies, such as [centaurs](/Centaur \"Centaur\"). Though a scarf of [repulsion](/Repulsion \"Repulsion\") is typically better suited for this task, repulsion has no effect on attacks like an orc priest's [Smiting](/Smiting \"Smiting\").\n- Characters reliant on ranged attacks might still find the scarf useful, though you'll have less range to blast enemies before they get to you.\n\n## History\n\n- Scarves of shadows were added in [0.26](/0.26 \"0.26\"). In this version only, scarves of shadows would reduce your [spellpower](/Spellpower \"Spellpower\").\n","html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html class=\"client-nojs\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/>\n<title>Shadows - CrawlWiki</title>\n<script>document.documentElement.className = document.documentElement.className.replace( /(^|\\s)client-nojs(\\s|$)/, \"$1client-js$2\" );</script>\n<script>(window.RLQ=window.RLQ||[]).push(function(){mw.config.set({\"wgCanonicalNamespace\":\"\",\"wgCanonicalSpeci